# Review Checklist

Run this before committing or opening a PR for any non-trivial change in
{{PROJECT_NAME}}. It is the per-change gate; the deeper
[architecture review](/{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/architecture-review-checklist.md)
applies when you change boundaries or ownership.

## Scope and ownership

- [ ] The change matches exactly one task (or an explicitly approved batch).
- [ ] Mechanical moves/renames and semantic edits are **not** mixed in one commit.
- [ ] No unrelated drive-by changes snuck in; the diff is reviewable.

## Correctness and tests

- [ ] Tests were added or updated for every behavior change.
- [ ] The strongest relevant verification was run: `{{TEST_CMD}}`.
- [ ] Pass rate is preserved or improved (or a temporary shim is documented).
- [ ] Failure paths and edge cases are handled, not just the happy path.

## Documentation and tasks

- [ ] Docs and task records are updated in the same change (see
      [docs-sync-policy](/{{DOCS_AGENT_DIR}}/docs-sync-policy.md)).
- [ ] Moved files have their references/links updated.
- [ ] The task file's checkboxes reflect reality; a finished task is moved to
      `tasks/done/` with completion metadata.

## CI and temporary shims

- [ ] Structural checks pass for touched scope
      (`python3 {{TOOLS_DIR}}/check.py --strict`, or the shipped
      `{{CHECKS_DIR}}/` scripts directly).
- [ ] Any temporary shim is tracked by a current task under `tasks/active/`
      with a specific removal task id.
- [ ] Commit message explains *why*, not just *what*.
